Task 1: Conduct a Vulnerability Assessment on a Demo Website
Description: Choose a demo website (e.g., DVWA or bWAPP) and identify vulnerabilities using tools like OWASP ZAP. Focus on SQL Injection and XSS.
Outcome: Proficiency in using web application vulnerability scanners and identifying critical vulnerabilities.

Task 2: Perform Manual Testing for Vulnerabilities
Description: Test for SQL Injection and XSS vulnerabilities manually using Burp Suite. Document successful exploits with evidence.
Outcome: Experience in manual testing for web vulnerabilities and preparing detailed exploit reports.

Task 3: Develop Remediation Recommendations
Description: Create a remediation plan for fixing identified vulnerabilities, such as implementing input validation and prepared statements.
Outcome: Ability to provide practical and effective recommendations to mitigate security risks.
